fordham university school of law (commonly known as fordham law or fordham law school) is a part of fordham university in the united states. the school is located in the borough of manhattan in new york city, and is one of eight aba-approved law schools in that city. in 2013, 91% of the law school's first-time test takers passed the bar exam, placing the law school fifth-best among new york's 15 law schools. according to fordham university school of law's 2014 aba-required disclosures, 67.8% of the class of 2014 obtained full-time, long-term, jd-required employment nine months after graduation.